message: "If you use this software or reference this work, please cite it as below."
title: "Boolean Algebra over Trapdoor Sets: A Practical Framework for Privacy-Preserving Set Operations with Probabilistic Guarantees"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Towell
    given-names: Alexander
    email: atowell@siue.edu
    affiliation: "Southern Illinois University Edwardsville"
repository-code: "https://github.com/queelius/oblivious-computing"
abstract: >-
  Hash-Based Oblivious Sets (HBOS) is a practical framework for privacy-preserving
  set operations that combines cryptographic hash functions with probabilistic data
  structures. Unlike traditional approaches using fully homomorphic encryption or
  secure multi-party computation, HBOS achieves microsecond-scale performance by
  embracing approximate operations with explicitly managed error rates.
keywords:
  - cryptographic hash functions
  - oblivious data structures
  - privacy-preserving computation
  - approximate algorithms
  - probabilistic data structures
  - Bernoulli types
